{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775860041216,"sessionID":"ses_2867e7541ffeWRc4IJHf3hGfjk","part":{"id":"prt_d7981b125001mkT5x0ysGHZto1","messageID":"msg_d79819f10001PAcUWKzRcsVDgn","sessionID":"ses_2867e7541ffeWRc4IJHf3hGfjk","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_a70bc0eeccc44dd1827def52","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-016/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-016/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Proposal: PicoD File Management API (AR-016)\n2: \n3: ## Summary\n4: \n5: Implement the file management API for the PicoD module in `pkg/picod`, providing secure file operations within sandboxed environments including read, write, list, and delete capabilities with proper security validations and resource limits.\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## Purpose\n10: \n11: The PicoD File Management API provides:\n12: \n13: 1. **Secure File Operations**: Read, write, list, and delete files within controlled sandbox directories\n14: 2. **Path Validation**: Ensure all file operations stay within allowed workspace boundaries\n15: 3. **Resource Limits**: Enforce file size limits, directory depth limits, and quota management\n16: 4. **Atomic Operations**: Support for atomic write operations to prevent partial writes\n17: 5. **Metadata Access**: Retrieve file metadata (size, modification time, permissions)\n18: \n19: This implementation builds upon the command execution infrastructure from AR-015 and provides the file management layer needed for code interpreters and agent runtimes to interact with the filesystem safely.\n20: \n21: ---\n22: \n23: ## Scope\n24: \n25: ### In Scope\n26: \n27: - `pkg/picod/filesystem.go` - File operations interface and implementation\n28: - `pkg/picod/fileinfo.go` - File metadata and information structures\n29: - `pkg/picod/quota.go` - Disk quota management and enforcement\n30: - `pkg/picod/path.go` - Path validation and normalization utilities\n31: - `pkg/picod/filesystem_test.go` - File operation unit tests\n32: - `pkg/picod/quota_test.go` - Quota management tests\n33: - `pkg/picod/path_test.go` - Path validation tests\n34: - `pkg/picod/integration_test.go` - Integration tests (extended)\n35: \n36: ### Out of Scope\n37: \n38: - Network filesystem support (NFS, SMB, etc.)\n39: - File watching/notification systems\n40: - Advanced permissions (ACLs, extended attributes)\n41: - File encryption/decryption\n42: - Distributed file locking\n43: - Backup and snapshot functionality\n44: \n45: ---\n46: \n47: ## Impact Analysis\n48: \n49: ### Dependencies\n50: \n51: | Package | Purpose |\n52: |---------|---------|\n53: | `os` | File operations and metadata |\n54: | `io` | Stream operations |\n55: | `io/fs` | Filesystem interfaces |\n56: | `path/filepath` | Path manipulation |\n57: | `context` | Operation cancellation and timeouts |\n58: | `syscall` | Low-level filesystem operations |\n59: | `k8s.io/klog/v2` | Structured logging |\n60: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/picod` | Existing PicoD types and limits |\n61: \n62: ### Affected Components\n63: \n64: 1. **Code Interpreter**: Will use file API for reading/writing code files and outputs\n65: 2. **Agent Runtime**: Will use file API for accessing configuration and state files\n66: 3. **Workload Manager**: Will use file API for managing job artifacts\n67: 4. **Sandbox Manager**: Will configure filesystem quotas and permissions\n68: 5. **Security Module**: Will validate file operation permissions\n69: \n70: ### Backward Compatibility\n71: \n72: - This is a new API surface within the existing PicoD module\n73: - No breaking changes to existing AR-015 command execution APIs\n74: - Extends PicoD struct with additional methods\n75: - Configuration via environment variables and programmatic API\n76: \n77: ### Risk Assessment\n78: \n79: | Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |\n80: |------|------------|--------|------------|\n81: | Path traversal attack | Medium | Critical | Strict path validation, chroot-style isolation |\n82: | Disk space exhaustion | High | High | Enforce quotas, validate write sizes |\n83: | Symlink attacks | Medium | High | Resolve and validate symlink targets |\n84: | Race conditions | Medium | Medium | Atomic operations where possible, proper locking |\n85: | Information disclosure | Low | High | Validate read operations, enforce permissions |\n86: | Directory depth attacks | Low | Medium | Enforce maximum directory depth limits |\n87: \n88: ---\n89: \n90: ## Alternatives Considered\n91: \n92: ### Alternative 1: Use os.* Directly\n93: \n94: **Approach**: Expose standard library `os` package functions directly\n95: \n96: **Pros**:\n97: - Minimal implementation effort\n98: - No additional abstraction layer\n99: - Full control for callers\n100: \n101: **Cons**:\n102: - No security enforcement\n103: - No quota management\n104: - Easy to misuse\n105: - Hard to audit file operations\n106: \n107: **Decision**: Wrap with security and quota validation layer.\n108: \n109: ### Alternative 2: In-Memory Filesystem (afero)\n110: \n111: **Approach**: Use afero or similar in-memory filesystem abstraction\n112: \n113: **Pros**:\n114: - Easy testing and mocking\n115: - Built-in abstraction layer\n116: - Additional safety\n117: \n118: **Cons**:\n119: - Additional dependency\n120: - Doesn't match real filesystem behavior exactly\n121: - May not support all operations needed\n122: \n123: **Decision**: Use real filesystem with validation for production accuracy.\n124: \n125: ### Alternative 3: Container-mounted Volumes\n126: \n127: **Approach**: Delegate file operations to container runtime volume mounts\n128: \n129: **Pros**:\n130: - Leverages container isolation\n131: - No additional code to maintain\n132: - Clear security boundary\n133: \n134: **Cons**:\n135: - Requires container runtime integration\n136: - Less flexible for non-container deployments\n137: - More complex orchestration\n138: \n139: **Decision**: Implement native file operations; container integration can be added later.\n140: \n141: ---\n142: \n143: ## Implementation Details\n144: \n145: ### File Quota\n146: \n147: ```go\n148: type FileQuota struct {\n149:     // MaxFileSize is the maximum size of a single file in bytes\n150:     MaxFileSize int64\n151:     \n152:     // MaxTotalSize is the maximum total size of all files in bytes\n153:     MaxTotalSize int64\n154:     \n155:     // MaxFiles is the maximum number of files allowed\n156:     MaxFiles int64\n157:     \n158:     // MaxDirectoryDepth is the maximum directory depth\n159:     MaxDirectoryDepth int\n160: }\n161: ```\n162: \n163: ### FileInfo\n164: \n165: ```go\n166: type FileInfo struct {\n167:     // Name is the file name\n168:     Name string\n169:     \n170:     // Path is the full path within the sandbox\n171:     Path string\n172:     \n173:     // Size is the file size in bytes\n174:     Size int64\n175:     \n176:     // Mode is the file mode and permissions\n177:     Mode os.FileMode\n178:     \n179:     // ModTime is the last modification time\n180:     ModTime time.Time\n181:     \n182:     // IsDir indicates if this is a directory\n183:     IsDir bool\n184:     \n185:     // FileType indicates the file type (regular, symlink, etc.)\n186:     FileType FileType\n187: }\n188: \n189: type FileType string\n190: \n191: const (\n192:     FileTypeRegular   FileType = \"regular\"\n193:     FileTypeDirectory FileType = \"directory\"\n194:     FileTypeSymlink   FileType = \"symlink\"\n195:     FileTypeOther     FileType = \"other\"\n196: )\n197: ```\n198: \n199: ### File Operations Interface\n200: \n201: ```go\n202: type FileSystem interface {\n203:     // Read reads the entire contents of a file\n204:     Read(ctx context.Context, path string) ([]byte, error)\n205:     \n206:     // ReadStream reads a file with streaming support\n207:     ReadStream(ctx context.Context, path string) (io.ReadCloser, error)\n208:     \n209:     // Write writes data to a file atomically\n210:     Write(ctx context.Context, path string, data []byte) error\n211:     \n212:     // WriteStream writes from a stream with size limit\n213:     WriteStream(ctx context.Context, path string, reader io.Reader, size int64) error\n214:     \n215:     // Delete removes a file or empty directory\n216:     Delete(ctx context.Context, path string) error\n217:     \n218:     // DeleteAll removes a directory and all contents\n219:     DeleteAll(ctx context.Context, path string) error\n220:     \n221:     // Exists checks if a path exists\n222:     Exists(ctx context.Context, path string) (bool, error)\n223:     \n224:     // Info returns file metadata\n225:     Info(ctx context.Context, path string) (*FileInfo, error)\n226:     \n227:     // List lists directory contents\n228:     List(ctx context.Context, path string) ([]FileInfo, error)\n229:     \n230:     // Mkdir creates a directory\n231:     Mkdir(ctx context.Context, path string, perm os.FileMode) error\n232:     \n233:     // MkdirAll creates a directory and all parent directories\n234:     MkdirAll(ctx context.Context, path string, perm os.FileMode) error\n235:     \n236:     // Rename renames/moves a file or directory\n237:     Rename(ctx context.Context, oldPath, newPath string) error\n238:     \n239:     // Copy copies a file\n240:     Copy(ctx context.Context, srcPath, dstPath string) error\n241:     \n242:     // Quota returns current quota usage\n243:     Quota(ctx context.Context) (*QuotaUsage, error)\n244: }\n245: ```\n246: \n247: ### Quota Usage\n248: \n249: ```go\n250: type QuotaUsage struct {\n251:     // UsedBytes is the total bytes used\n252:     UsedBytes int64\n253:     \n254:     // MaxBytes is the maximum bytes allowed\n255:     MaxBytes int64\n256:     \n257:     // FileCount is the number of files\n258:     FileCount int64\n259:     \n260:     // MaxFiles is the maximum files allowed\n261:     MaxFiles int64\n262:     \n263:     // PercentUsed is the percentage of quota used (0-100)\n264:     PercentUsed float64\n265: }\n266: ```\n267: \n268: ### PicoD Integration\n269: \n270: ```go\n271: // PicoD struct extended with filesystem\n272: type PicoD struct {\n273:     sandboxID    string\n274:     workDir      string\n275:     limits       *ResourceLimits\n276:     securityOpts *SecurityOptions\n277:     fileQuota    *FileQuota\n278:     logger       klog.Logger\n279:     \n280:     // File system operations\n281:     fs FileSystem\n282: }\n283: \n284: // FileSystem returns the file system interface\n285: func (p *PicoD) FileSystem() FileSystem\n286: \n287: // Convenience methods on PicoD\n288: func (p *PicoD) ReadFile(ctx context.Context, path string) ([]byte, error)\n289: func (p *PicoD) WriteFile(ctx context.Context, path string, data []byte) error\n290: func (p *PicoD) ListDir(ctx context.Context, path string) ([]FileInfo, error)\n291: func (p *PicoD) DeleteFile(ctx context.Context, path string) error\n292: func (p *PicoD) GetQuota(ctx context.Context) (*QuotaUsage, error)\n293: ```\n294: \n295: ### Path Validation\n296: \n297: ```go\n298: // ValidatePath validates a path is within the workspace\n299: func ValidatePath(path, workDir string) (string, error)\n300: \n301: // ResolvePath resolves a path to absolute, following symlinks\n302: func ResolvePath(path string) (string, error)\n303: \n304: // GetDepth returns the directory depth of a path\n305: func GetDepth(path string) int\n306: \n307: // IsWithinWorkspace checks if resolved path is within workspace\n308: func IsWithinWorkspace(path, workDir string) bool\n309: ```\n310: \n311: ### Atomic Write Implementation\n312: \n313: ```go\n314: // Write atomically writes data to a file\n315: func (fs *fileSystem) Write(ctx context.Context, path string, data []byte) error {\n316:     // 1. Validate path\n317:     absPath, err := ValidatePath(path, fs.workDir)\n318:     if err != nil {\n319:         return err\n320:     }\n321:     \n322:     // 2. Check quota\n323:     if int64(len(data)) > fs.quota.MaxFileSize {\n324:         return &FileError{\n325:             Type:    FileErrorQuotaExceeded,\n326:             Message: \"file size exceeds quota\",\n327:         }\n328:     }\n329:     \n330:     // 3. Write to temporary file\n331:     tmpPath := absPath + \".tmp.\" + uuid()\n332:     if err := os.WriteFile(tmpPath, data, 0644); err != nil {\n333:         return &FileError{\n334:             Type:    FileErrorWrite,\n335:             Message: \"failed to write file\",\n336:             Underlying: err,\n337:         }\n338:     }\n339:     \n340:     // 4. Atomic rename\n341:     if err := os.Rename(tmpPath, absPath); err != nil {\n342:         os.Remove(tmpPath) // Cleanup\n343:         return &FileError{\n344:             Type:    FileErrorWrite,\n345:             Message: \"failed to rename file\",\n346:             Underlying: err,\n347:         }\n348:     }\n349:     \n350:     return nil\n351: }\n352: ```\n353: \n354: ---\n355: \n356: ## Configuration Reference\n357: \n358: ### Environment Variables\n359: \n360: | Variable | Required | Default | Notes |\n361: |----------|----------|---------|-------|\n362: | `PICOD_QUOTA_MAX_FILE_SIZE` | No | `10MB` | Maximum single file size |\n363: | `PICOD_QUOTA_MAX_TOTAL_SIZE` | No | `100MB` | Maximum total storage |\n364: | `PICOD_QUOTA_MAX_FILES` | No | `1000` | Maximum number of files |\n365: | `PICOD_QUOTA_MAX_DEPTH` | No | `10` | Maximum directory depth |\n366: | `PICOD_WORKDIR` | No | `/tmp/picod` | Base working directory |\n367: \n368: ### Example Configuration\n369: \n370: ```go\n371: quota := &FileQuota{\n372:     MaxFileSize:       10 * 1024 * 1024,  // 10 MiB\n373:     MaxTotalSize:      100 * 1024 * 1024, // 100 MiB\n374:     MaxFiles:          1000,\n375:     MaxDirectoryDepth: 10,\n376: }\n377: ```\n378: \n379: ---\n380: \n381: ## Testing Strategy\n382: \n383: ### Unit Tests\n384: \n385: | Test | Purpose |\n386: |------|---------|\n387: | `TestFileSystem_Read_Success` | Basic file read |\n388: | `TestFileSystem_Read_NotFound` | Read non-existent file |\n389: | `TestFileSystem_Read_PathTraversal` | Path traversal blocked |\n390: | `TestFileSystem_Write_Success` | Basic file write |\n391: | `TestFileSystem_Write_Atomic` | Atomic write verification |\n392: | `TestFileSystem_Write_QuotaExceeded` | Write exceeds quota |\n393: | `TestFileSystem_Delete_Success` | Delete file |\n394: | `TestFileSystem_Delete_All` | Delete directory recursively |\n395: | `TestFileSystem_Exists` | Check file existence |\n396: | `TestFileSystem_Info` | Get file metadata |\n397: | `TestFileSystem_List` | List directory contents |\n398: | `TestFileSystem_Mkdir` | Create directories |\n399: | `TestFileSystem_Rename` | Rename/move files |\n400: | `TestFileSystem_Copy` | Copy files |\n401: | `TestFileSystem_Quota` | Quota usage tracking |\n402: | `TestValidatePath_Success` | Valid paths accepted |\n403: | `TestValidatePath_PathTraversal` | Path traversal rejected |\n404: | `TestValidatePath_Symlink` | Symlink validation |\n405: | `TestGetDepth` | Directory depth calculation |\n406: \n407: ### Integration Tests\n408: \n409: | Test | Purpose |\n410: |------|---------|\n411: | `TestFileSystem_Integration_FullLifecycle` | Full file operation lifecycle |\n412: | `TestFileSystem_Integration_Concurrent` | Concurrent file operations |\n413: | `TestFileSystem_Integration_QuotaEnforcement` | Verify quotas are enforced |\n414: | `TestFileSystem_Integration_AtomicWrite` | Atomic write under load |\n415: | `TestFileSystem_Integration_LargeFiles` | Handle files near size limit |\n416: \n417: ### Test Fixtures\n418: \n419: ```go\n420: // mockFileSystem creates a test file system\n421: func mockFileSystem(t *testing.T, quota *FileQuota) (FileSystem, func()) {\n422:     tmpDir := t.TempDir()\n423:     fs := NewFileSystem(tmpDir, quota, klog.Background())\n424:     cleanup := func() {}\n425:     return fs, cleanup\n426: }\n427: \n428: // createTestFile creates a test file with given size\n429: func createTestFile(fs FileSystem, path string, size int64) error {\n430:     data := make([]byte, size)\n431:     for i := range data {\n432:         data[i] = byte(i % 256)\n433:     }\n434:     return fs.Write(context.Background(), path, data)\n435: }\n436: ```\n437: \n438: ---\n439: \n440: ## Acceptance Criteria\n441: \n442: - [ ] `FileSystem` interface implements all required methods\n443: - [ ] Path validation prevents operations outside workspace\n444: - [ ] Quota enforcement works correctly (size, file count, depth)\n445: - [ ] Atomic writes prevent partial file corruption\n446: - [ ] Symlink attacks are prevented\n447: - [ ] All unit tests pass\n448: - [ ] Integration tests pass\n449: - [ ] Code coverage >= 80%\n450: - [ ] Documentation includes usage examples\n451: - [ ] Error types are properly classified and documented\n452: - [ ] File operations are logged for audit trail\n453: \n454: ---\n455: \n456: ## Error Handling\n457: \n458: ### FileError\n459: \n460: ```go\n461: type FileError struct {\n462:     Type       FileErrorType\n463:     Message    string\n464:     Underlying error\n465: }\n466: \n467: type FileErrorType string\n468: \n469: const (\n470:     FileErrorNotFound      FileErrorType = \"not_found\"\n471:     FileErrorPermission    FileErrorType = \"permission\"\n472:     FileErrorQuotaExceeded FileErrorType = \"quota_exceeded\"\n473:     FileErrorPathTraversal FileErrorType = \"path_traversal\"\n474:     FileErrorWrite         FileErrorType = \"write\"\n475:     FileErrorRead          FileErrorType = \"read\"\n476:     FileErrorSymlink       FileErrorType = \"symlink\"\n477:     FileErrorDepth         FileErrorType = \"depth_exceeded\"\n478: )\n479: ```\n480: \n481: ### Error Conditions\n482: \n483: | Condition | Error Type | HTTP Mapping | Description |\n484: |-----------|------------|--------------|-------------|\n485: | File does not exist | `FileErrorNotFound` | 404 Not Found | Requested file was not found |\n486: | Path outside workspace | `FileErrorPathTraversal` | 403 Forbidden | Path validation failed |\n487: | Quota exceeded | `FileErrorQuotaExceeded` | 413 Payload Too Large | File/quota limit exceeded |\n488: | Permission denied | `FileErrorPermission` | 403 Forbidden | Insufficient permissions |\n489: | Symlink attack | `FileErrorSymlink` | 403 Forbidden | Symlink target outside workspace |\n490: | Directory depth exceeded | `FileErrorDepth` | 400 Bad Request | Path exceeds max depth |\n491: | Write failure | `FileErrorWrite` | 500 Internal Server Error | Failed to write file |\n492: | Read failure | `FileErrorRead` | 500 Internal Server Error | Failed to read file |\n493: \n494: ---\n495: \n496: ## References\n497: \n498: - AR-015: PicoD Command Execution API\n499: - AR-012: Sandbox Infrastructure\n500: - `pkg/picod/design.md`: PicoD Design Document\n501: - `pkg/picod/tasks.md`: PicoD Task List (AR-015)\n502: - `code-execution/spec.md`: PicoD Specification\n\n(End of file - total 502 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Proposal: PicoD File Management API (AR-016)\n\n## Summary\n\nImplement the file management API for the PicoD module in `pkg/picod`, providing secure file operations within sandboxed environments including read, write, list, and delete capabilities with proper security validations and resource limits.\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nThe PicoD File Management API provides:\n\n1. **Secure File Operations**: Read, write, list, and delete files within controlled sandbox directories\n2. **Path Validation**: Ensure all file operations stay within allowed workspace boundaries\n3. **Resource Limits**: Enforce file size limits, directory depth limits, and quota management\n4. **Atomic Operations**: Support for atomic write operations to prevent partial writes\n5. **Metadata Access**: Retrieve file metadata (size, modification time, permissions)\n\nThis implementation builds upon the command execution infrastructure from AR-015 and provides the file management layer needed for code interpreters and agent runtimes to interact with the filesystem safely.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-016/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775860041166,"end":1775860041212}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775860041219,"sessionID":"ses_2867e7541ffeWRc4IJHf3hGfjk","part":{"id":"prt_d7981bbd8001s7qRzzPAw0b2t1","messageID":"msg_d79819f10001PAcUWKzRcsVDgn","sessionID":"ses_2867e7541ffeWRc4IJHf3hGfjk","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_53034ed4d05e4cc4b5fbcfed","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/picod/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/picod/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-015 — PicoD Command Execution API Tasks\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-015 — PicoD Command Execution API |\n8: | Module | `pkg/picod` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: | Stage | ST-3 completed |\n12: \n13: ## Atomic Tasks\n14: \n15: ### Phase 1: Core Data Structures & Types\n16: \n17: - [ ] **TASK-001**: Define `ResourceLimits` struct in `pkg/picod/limits.go`\n18:   - Fields: `Timeout` (time.Duration), `MaxCPU` (float64), `MaxMemory` (int64), `MaxOutputSize` (int64), `MaxProcesses` (int)\n19:   - Method: `Validate()` returning error\n20:   - Validation rules: Timeout > 0, MaxCPU >= 0, MaxMemory > 0, MaxOutputSize > 0, MaxProcesses > 0\n21: \n22: - [ ] **TASK-002**: Define `DefaultResourceLimits()` function in `pkg/picod/limits.go`\n23:   - Returns: Timeout=30s, MaxCPU=1.0, MaxMemory=128MiB, MaxOutputSize=10MiB, MaxProcesses=10\n24: \n25: - [ ] **TASK-003**: Define `SecurityOptions` struct in `pkg/picod/security.go`\n26:   - Fields: `UID` (int), `GID` (int), `Capabilities` ([]string), `ReadOnlyFS` (bool), `NoNetwork` (bool), `AllowedCommands` ([]string)\n27:   - Method: `Validate()` returning error\n28: \n29: - [ ] **TASK-004**: Define `DefaultSecurityOpts()` function in `pkg/picod/security.go`\n30:   - Returns: UID/GID=-1 (no change), Capabilities=nil, ReadOnlyFS=false, NoNetwork=true, AllowedCommands=nil\n31: \n32: - [ ] **TASK-005**: Define `Command` struct in `pkg/picod/executor.go`\n33:   - Fields: `Path` (string), `Args` ([]string), `Env` ([]string), `Dir` (string), `Stdin` (io.Reader), `Stdout` (io.Writer), `Stderr` (io.Writer)\n34: \n35: - [ ] **TASK-006**: Define `CommandResult` struct in `pkg/picod/executor.go`\n36:   - Fields: `ExitCode` (int), `Stdout` ([]byte), `Stderr` ([]byte), `Duration` (time.Duration), `OOMKilled` (bool), `Timeout` (bool)\n37: \n38: - [ ] **TASK-007**: Define `ExecutionErrorType` and error constants in `pkg/picod/errors.go`\n39:   - Types: `ExecutionErrorTimeout`, `ExecutionErrorOOM`, `ExecutionErrorCancelled`, `ExecutionErrorSecurity`, `ExecutionErrorResource`, `ExecutionErrorExec`\n40: \n41: - [ ] **TASK-008**: Define `ExecutionError` struct in `pkg/picod/errors.go`\n42:   - Fields: `Type` (ExecutionErrorType), `Message` (string), `Underlying` (error)\n43:   - Methods: `Error()`, `Unwrap()`\n44: \n45: ### Phase 2: PicoD Core Implementation\n46: \n47: - [ ] **TASK-010**: Define `PicoD` struct in `pkg/picod/picod.go`\n48:   - Fields: `sandboxID` (string), `workDir` (string), `limits` (*ResourceLimits), `securityOpts` (*SecurityOptions), `logger` (klog.Logger)\n49: \n50: - [ ] **TASK-011**: Define `Option` type and functional options in `pkg/picod/picod.go`\n51:   - Options: `WithWorkDir()`, `WithLimits()`, `WithSecurityOpts()`, `WithLogger()`\n52: \n53: - [ ] **TASK-012**: Implement `New()` function in `pkg/picod/picod.go`\n54:   - Creates PicoD with defaults, applies options\n55:   - Default workDir: `/tmp/picod/{sandboxID}`\n56: \n57: - [ ] **TASK-013**: Implement `Config` struct and `LoadConfig()` in `pkg/picod/config.go`\n58:   - Loads from environment variables: PICOD_WORKDIR, PICOD_DEFAULT_TIMEOUT, PICOD_MAX_MEMORY, PICOD_MAX_CPU, PICOD_MAX_OUTPUT_SIZE, PICOD_MAX_PROCESSES\n59:   - Applies defaults when env vars not set\n60: \n61: ### Phase 3: Command Execution\n62: \n63: - [ ] **TASK-020**: Implement `Run()` method in `pkg/picod/executor.go`\n64:   - Flow: ValidateCommand → Create exec.Cmd → Apply resource limits → Capture output → Start → Wait → Build result\n65:   - Handle timeout, OOM, cancellation detection\n66:   - Return *CommandResult and error\n67: \n68: - [ ] **TASK-021**: Implement `Start()` method in `pkg/picod/executor.go`\n69:   - Starts command without waiting\n70:   - Returns *Process\n71: \n72: - [ ] **TASK-022**: Define `Process` struct in `pkg/picod/process.go`\n73:   - Fields: `PID` (int), `cmd` (*exec.Cmd), `startTime` (time.Time)\n74:   - Methods: `Wait()`, `Kill()`, `Signal()`\n75: \n76: - [ ] **TASK-023**: Implement `Wait()` method for Process\n77:   - Waits for process completion\n78:   - Builds and returns CommandResult\n79: \n80: - [ ] **TASK-024**: Implement `Kill()` and `Signal()` methods for Process\n81:   - Sends signals to process\n82: \n83: ### Phase 4: Resource Limit Enforcement\n84: \n85: - [ ] **TASK-030**: Implement `Apply()` method for ResourceLimits in `pkg/picod/limits.go`\n86:   - Applies memory limits via syscall.Setrlimit (RLIMIT_AS)\n87:   - Applies process limits via syscall.Setrlimit (RLIMIT_NPROC)\n88:   - Configures cmd.SysProcAttr for process group\n89: \n90: - [ ] **TASK-031**: Implement CPU limit enforcement logic\n91:   - Use cgroups for CPU limits (Linux-specific)\n92:   - Fallback gracefully on non-Linux platforms\n93: \n94: ### Phase 5: Security Validation\n95: \n96: - [ ] **TASK-040**: Implement `ValidateCommand()` function in `pkg/picod/security.go`\n97:   - Checks command against AllowedCommands allowlist\n98:   - Validates working directory is within workspace\n99:   - Checks for path traversal in arguments\n100:   - Validates environment variables (blocks LD_PRELOAD, LD_LIBRARY_PATH)\n101: \n102: - [ ] **TASK-041**: Implement `IsPathSafe()` function in `pkg/picod/security.go`\n103:   - Checks if path is within allowed workspace using filepath.Abs and strings.HasPrefix\n104: \n105: - [ ] **TASK-042**: Implement `DropPrivileges()` function in `pkg/picod/security.go`\n106:   - Drops privileges to specified UID/GID using syscall.Setuid/Setgid\n107: \n108: ### Phase 6: Output Handling\n109: \n110: - [ ] **TASK-050**: Define `OutputHandler` interface in `pkg/picod/output.go`\n111:   - Methods: `OnStdout([]byte)`, `OnStderr([]byte)`, `OnComplete(*CommandResult)`\n112: \n113: - [ ] **TASK-051**: Implement `RunWithStreaming()` method in `pkg/picod/executor.go`\n114:   - Executes command with streaming output\n115:   - Calls handler callbacks as data becomes available\n116: \n117: ### Phase 7: Unit Tests\n118: \n119: - [ ] **TEST-001**: Create `TestResourceLimits_Validate` in `pkg/picod/limits_test.go`\n120:   - Valid limits → no error\n121:   - Timeout=0 → error\n122:   - MaxMemory<=0 → error\n123:   - MaxOutputSize<=0 → error\n124:   - MaxProcesses<=0 → error\n125: \n126: - [ ] **TEST-002**: Create `TestSecurityOptions_Validate` in `pkg/picod/security_test.go`\n127:   - Valid options → no error\n128:   - Invalid UID/GID → error\n129: \n130: - [ ] **TEST-003**: Create `TestPicoD_New` in `pkg/picod/picod_test.go`\n131:   - Default initialization\n132:   - WithWorkDir option\n133:   - WithLimits option\n134:   - WithSecurityOpts option\n135:   - WithLogger option\n136: \n137: - [ ] **TEST-004**: Create `TestPicoD_Run_Success` in `pkg/picod/executor_test.go`\n138:   - Execute simple command (echo)\n139:   - Verify ExitCode=0, Stdout captured\n140: \n141: - [ ] **TEST-005**: Create `TestPicoD_Run_Timeout` in `pkg/picod/executor_test.go`\n142:   - Command exceeds timeout\n143:   - Verify Timeout=true in result\n144:   - Verify ExecutionErrorTimeout returned\n145: \n146: - [ ] **TEST-006**: Create `TestPicoD_Run_Cancelled` in `pkg/picod/executor_test.go`\n147:   - Context cancelled before command completes\n148:   - Verify ExecutionErrorCancelled returned\n149: \n150: - [ ] **TEST-007**: Create `TestPicoD_OutputCapture` in `pkg/picod/executor_test.go`\n151:   - Capture stdout and stderr\n152:   - Verify correct output in CommandResult\n153: \n154: - [ ] **TEST-008**: Create `TestPicoD_SecurityValidation` in `pkg/picod/executor_test.go`\n155:   - Command not in allowlist → ExecutionErrorSecurity\n156:   - Path traversal in args → ExecutionErrorSecurity\n157:   - Dangerous env var → ExecutionErrorSecurity\n158: \n159: - [ ] **TEST-009**: Create `TestPicoD_ExecutionErrorTypes` in `pkg/picod/errors_test.go`\n160:   - Verify error type classification\n161:   - Verify Error() and Unwrap() work correctly\n162: \n163: - [ ] **TEST-010**: Create `TestProcess_Wait` in `pkg/picod/process_test.go`\n164:   - Start process, wait for completion\n165:   - Verify CommandResult built correctly\n166: \n167: - [ ] **TEST-011**: Create `TestProcess_Kill` in `pkg/picod/process_test.go`\n168:   - Start process, send kill signal\n169:   - Verify process terminated\n170: \n171: - [ ] **TEST-012**: Create `TestLoadConfig` in `pkg/picod/config_test.go`\n172:   - Load from environment variables\n173:   - Verify defaults applied when env vars not set\n174: \n175: - [ ] **TEST-013**: Create `TestIsPathSafe` in `pkg/picod/security_test.go`\n176:   - Safe paths → true\n177:   - Path traversal → false\n178:   - Absolute path outside workspace → false\n179: \n180: - [ ] **TEST-014**: Create `TestRunWithStreaming` in `pkg/picod/output_test.go`\n181:   - Streaming output captured via handler\n182:   - Verify OnStdout/OnStderr/OnComplete called\n183: \n184: ### Phase 8: Integration Tests\n185: \n186: - [ ] **TEST-020**: Create `TestPicoD_Integration_FullLifecycle` in `pkg/picod/integration_test.go`\n187:   - Full execution flow with real commands\n188:   - Verify end-to-end functionality\n189: \n190: - [ ] **TEST-021**: Create `TestPicoD_Integration_Concurrent` in `pkg/picod/integration_test.go`\n191:   - Execute multiple commands concurrently\n192:   - Verify isolation and correct results\n193: \n194: - [ ] **TEST-022**: Create `TestPicoD_Integration_ResourceLimits` in `pkg/picod/integration_test.go`\n195:   - Create memory-intensive command\n196:   - Verify OOM killed when exceeds limit\n197: \n198: - [ ] **TEST-023**: Create `TestPicoD_Integration_Streaming` in `pkg/picod/integration_test.go`\n199:   - Long-running command with streaming output\n200:   - Verify handler receives all output\n201: \n202: ### Phase 9: Documentation\n203: \n204: - [ ] **DOC-001**: Add Go doc comments to all public types and functions\n205:   - Include usage examples in doc comments\n206: \n207: - [ ] **DOC-002**: Create `pkg/picod/README.md`\n208:   - Architecture overview\n209:   - Usage examples\n210:   - Configuration options\n211:   - Error handling guide\n212: \n213: - [ ] **DOC-003**: Add API examples to handler doc comments\n214:   - Example: creating PicoD instance\n215:   - Example: running command\n216:   - Example: streaming output\n217: \n218: ## Acceptance Criteria\n219: \n220: - [ ] PicoD struct implements all required methods\n221: - [ ] Resource limits enforced (timeout, CPU, memory, output size)\n222: - [ ] Output capture works correctly (stdout, stderr, exit code)\n223: - [ ] Cancellation via context is supported\n224: - [ ] Security validations prevent dangerous operations\n225: - [ ] Streaming output is supported\n226: - [ ] All unit tests pass\n227: - [ ] Integration tests pass\n228: - [ ] Code coverage >= 80%\n229: - [ ] Documentation includes usage examples\n230: - [ ] Error types properly classified and documented\n231: - [ ] Each .go file has corresponding _test.go file\n232: \n233: ## Dependencies\n234: \n235: | Dependency | Status |\n236: |------------|--------|\n237: | Go 1.21+ | Required |\n238: | k8s.io/klog/v2 | Required |\n239: | context package | Required |\n240: | os/exec package | Required |\n241: | syscall package | Required |\n242: | AR-012 (Sandbox Infrastructure) | Completed |\n243: | AR-013 (Session Storage) | Completed |\n244: | AR-014 (Valkey Storage) | Completed |\n245: \n246: ## Test Infrastructure\n247: \n248: - [ ] **TEST-030**: Create `testEnv` struct for unit tests\n249:   - Mock logger\n250:   - Temporary test directories\n251: \n252: - [ ] **TEST-031**: Create mock OutputHandler for testing\n253:   - Track OnStdout/OnStderr/OnComplete calls\n254: \n255: ## Coverage Verification\n256: \n257: - [ ] **COV-001**: Run coverage check\n258:   - Command: `go test -race -v -coverprofile=coverage.out -coverpkg=./pkg/picod/... ./pkg/picod/...`\n259:   - Verify code coverage >= 80%\n260:   - Verify each .go file has corresponding _test.go\n\n(End of file - total 260 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-015 — PicoD Command Execution API Tasks\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-015 — PicoD Command Execution API |\n| Module | `pkg/picod` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | M |\n| Stage | ST-3 completed |\n\n## Atomic Tasks\n\n### Phase 1: Core Data Structures & Types\n\n- [ ] **TASK-001**: Define `ResourceLimits` struct in `pkg/picod/limits.go`\n  - Fields: `Timeout` (time.Duration), `MaxCPU` (float64), `MaxMemory` (int64), `MaxOutputSize` (int64), `MaxProcesses` (int)\n  - Method: `Validate()` returning error\n  - Validation rules: Timeout > 0, MaxCPU >= 0, MaxMemory > 0, MaxOutputSize > 0, MaxProcesses > 0","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/picod/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775860041172,"end":1775860041217}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775860041221,"sessionID":"ses_2867e7541ffeWRc4IJHf3hGfjk","part":{"id":"prt_d7981c0b70017jafR1lpwOSA8t","messageID":"msg_d79819f10001PAcUWKzRcsVDgn","sessionID":"ses_2867e7541ffeWRc4IJHf3hGfjk","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_9ae6334566bb4377aa3e1321","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/picod/picod.go"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/picod/picod.go</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: package picod\n2: \n3: import (\n4: \t\"context\"\n5: \t\"fmt\"\n6: \t\"os\"\n7: \t\"path/filepath\"\n8: \n9: \t\"k8s.io/klog/v2\"\n10: )\n11: \n12: type PicoD struct {\n13: \tsandboxID    string\n14: \tworkDir      string\n15: \tlimits       *ResourceLimits\n16: \tsecurityOpts *SecurityOptions\n17: \texecutor     *Executor\n18: }\n19: \n20: type Option func(*PicoD)\n21: \n22: func New(sandboxID string, opts ...Option) *PicoD {\n23: \tp := &PicoD{\n24: \t\tsandboxID:    sandboxID,\n25: \t\tworkDir:      filepath.Join(\"/tmp/picod\", sandboxID),\n26: \t\tlimits:       DefaultResourceLimits(),\n27: \t\tsecurityOpts: DefaultSecurityOpts(),\n28: \t}\n29: \n30: \tfor _, opt := range opts {\n31: \t\topt(p)\n32: \t}\n33: \n34: \tp.securityOpts.WorkDir = p.workDir\n35: \tp.executor = NewExecutor(p.limits, p.securityOpts)\n36: \n37: \treturn p\n38: }\n39: \n40: func WithWorkDir(dir string) Option {\n41: \treturn func(p *PicoD) {\n42: \t\tp.workDir = dir\n43: \t}\n44: }\n45: \n46: func WithLimits(limits *ResourceLimits) Option {\n47: \treturn func(p *PicoD) {\n48: \t\tp.limits = limits\n49: \t}\n50: }\n51: \n52: func WithSecurityOpts(opts *SecurityOptions) Option {\n53: \treturn func(p *PicoD) {\n54: \t\tp.securityOpts = opts\n55: \t}\n56: }\n57: \n58: func WithLogger(logger klog.Logger) Option {\n59: \treturn func(p *PicoD) {\n60: \t\tklog.SetLogger(logger)\n61: \t}\n62: }\n63: \n64: func (p *PicoD) Run(ctx context.Context, cmd *Command) (*CommandResult, error) {\n65: \tklog.V(4).InfoS(\"executing command\", \"path\", cmd.Path, \"args\", cmd.Args)\n66: \n67: \tresult, err := p.executor.Run(ctx, cmd)\n68: \n69: \tif err != nil {\n70: \t\tklog.ErrorS(err, \"command execution failed\", \"path\", cmd.Path)\n71: \t} else {\n72: \t\tklog.V(4).InfoS(\"command completed\", \"path\", cmd.Path, \"exitCode\", result.ExitCode, \"duration\", result.Duration)\n73: \t}\n74: \n75: \treturn result, err\n76: }\n77: \n78: func (p *PicoD) Start(ctx context.Context, cmd *Command) (*Process, error) {\n79: \tklog.V(4).InfoS(\"starting command\", \"path\", cmd.Path, \"args\", cmd.Args)\n80: \n81: \tprocess, err := p.executor.Start(ctx, cmd)\n82: \tif err != nil {\n83: \t\tklog.ErrorS(err, \"failed to start command\", \"path\", cmd.Path)\n84: \t}\n85: \n86: \treturn process, err\n87: }\n88: \n89: func (p *PicoD) RunWithStreaming(ctx context.Context, cmd *Command, handler OutputHandler) (*CommandResult, error) {\n90: \tklog.V(4).InfoS(\"executing command with streaming\", \"path\", cmd.Path, \"args\", cmd.Args)\n91: \n92: \tresult, err := p.executor.RunWithStreaming(ctx, cmd, handler)\n93: \n94: \tif err != nil {\n95: \t\tklog.ErrorS(err, \"streaming command execution failed\", \"path\", cmd.Path)\n96: \t}\n97: \n98: \treturn result, err\n99: }\n100: \n101: func (p *PicoD) ensureWorkDir() error {\n102: \tif _, err := os.Stat(p.workDir); os.IsNotExist(err) {\n103: \t\tif err := os.MkdirAll(p.workDir, 0755); err != nil {\n104: \t\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"failed to create work directory: %w\", err)\n105: \t\t}\n106: \t}\n107: \treturn nil\n108: }\n109: \n110: func (p *PicoD) GetWorkDir() string {\n111: \treturn p.workDir\n112: }\n113: \n114: func (p *PicoD) GetSandboxID() string {\n115: \treturn p.sandboxID\n116: }\n\n(End of file - total 116 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"package picod\n\nimport (\n\t\"context\"\n\t\"fmt\"\n\t\"os\"\n\t\"path/filepath\"\n\n\t\"k8s.io/klog/v2\"\n)\n\ntype PicoD struct {\n\tsandboxID    string\n\tworkDir      string\n\tlimits       *ResourceLimits\n\tsecurityOpts *SecurityOptions\n\texecutor     *Executor\n}\n\ntype Option func(*PicoD)","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/picod/picod.go","time":{"start":1775860041174,"end":1775860041219}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775860041222,"sessionID":"ses_2867e7541ffeWRc4IJHf3hGfjk","part":{"id":"prt_d7981abac001l1frhlwIBdpyT4","messageID":"msg_d79819f10001PAcUWKzRcsVDgn","sessionID":"ses_2867e7541ffeWRc4IJHf3hGfjk","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_e1556d79f5c24e1796c806b5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-016/README.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-016/README.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-016 — PicoD 文件管理 API\n2: \n3: **Module:** pkg/picod  \n4: **Language:** Go  \n5: **Size:** M\n6: \n7: ## Summary\n8: \n9: Implement PicoD file management API for the pkg/picod module.\n10: \n11: ## Status\n12: \n13: - [x] Scaffold directory structure\n14: - [ ] Implement PicoD file management API\n15: - [ ] Add unit tests\n16: - [ ] Add integration tests\n17: \n18: ## Notes\n19: \n20: See `notes/` directory for implementation notes and decisions.\n21: \n22: ## Source Files\n23: \n24: See `src/` directory for source code changes.\n\n(End of file - total 24 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-016 — PicoD 文件管理 API\n\n**Module:** pkg/picod  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M\n\n## Summary\n\nImplement PicoD file management API for the pkg/picod module.\n\n## Status\n\n- [x] Scaffold directory structure\n- [ ] Implement PicoD file management API\n- [ ] Add unit tests\n- [ ] Add integration tests\n\n## Notes\n\nSee `notes/` directory for implementation notes and decisions.","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-016/README.md","time":{"start":1775860041163,"end":1775860041221}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775860041226,"sessionID":"ses_2867e7541ffeWRc4IJHf3hGfjk","part":{"id":"prt_d7981b6c900195w1YH7MCGESkf","messageID":"msg_d79819f10001PAcUWKzRcsVDgn","sessionID":"ses_2867e7541ffeWRc4IJHf3hGfjk","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_55ce4447da274ee3b484af4a","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/picod/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/picod/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Design: AR-015 PicoD Command Execution API\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-015 — PicoD Command Execution API |\n8: | Module | `pkg/picod` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: | Stage | ST-1 completed |\n12: \n13: This document describes the technical implementation for the PicoD command execution API within `pkg/picod`. The PicoD module provides secure, resource-limited command execution capabilities for the AgentCube platform, serving as the execution engine for code interpreters and agent runtimes.\n14: \n15: ## Architecture\n16: \n17: ### Component Structure\n18: \n19: ```\n20: pkg/picod/\n21: ├── picod.go                 # Main PicoD struct and initialization\n22: ├── picod_test.go            # PicoD unit tests\n23: ├── executor.go              # Command execution logic\n24: ├── executor_test.go         # Execution unit tests\n25: ├── limits.go                # Resource limit definitions and enforcement\n26: ├── limits_test.go           # Resource limit tests\n27: ├── security.go              # Security validation and hardening\n28: ├── security_test.go         # Security tests\n29: ├── output.go                # Output capture and streaming\n30: ├── output_test.go           # Output handling tests\n31: ├── process.go               # Running process management\n32: ├── process_test.go          # Process management tests\n33: ├── errors.go                # Error type definitions\n34: └── config.go                # Configuration from environment\n35: ```\n36: \n37: ### Integration Points\n38: \n39: - **os/exec**: Standard library command execution primitives\n40: - **syscall**: Process management, signals, and resource limits\n41: - **context**: Command cancellation and timeouts\n42: - **k8s.io/klog/v2**: Structured logging\n43: - **pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1**: Type definitions for CodeInterpreter\n44: - **pkg/common/types**: SandboxInfo type definitions\n45: \n46: ### Execution Flow\n47: \n48: ```\n49: Client (WorkloadManager/CodeInterpreter)\n50:   ↓\n51: PicoD.New(sandboxID, options...)\n52:   ↓\n53: PicoD.Run(ctx, Command)\n54:   ├─ ValidateCommand(cmd, securityOpts)\n55:   ├─ ApplyResourceLimits(limits)\n56:   ├─ exec.CommandContext(ctx, path, args...)\n57:   ├─ Configure cmd.SysProcAttr\n58:   ├─ Start process\n59:   ├─ Monitor with timeout/limits\n60:   ├─ Capture stdout/stderr\n61:   └─ Return CommandResult\n62: ```\n63: \n64: ## Data Structures\n65: \n66: ### PicoD\n67: \n68: ```go\n69: // PicoD represents a command execution sandbox\n70: type PicoD struct {\n71:     sandboxID    string\n72:     workDir      string\n73:     limits       *ResourceLimits\n74:     securityOpts *SecurityOptions\n75:     logger       klog.Logger\n76: }\n77: \n78: // Option is a functional option for PicoD\n79: type Option func(*PicoD)\n80: ```\n81: \n82: ### ResourceLimits\n83: \n84: ```go\n85: // ResourceLimits defines execution resource limits\n86: type ResourceLimits struct {\n87:     // Timeout is the maximum execution duration\n88:     Timeout time.Duration\n89:     \n90:     // MaxCPU is the maximum CPU cores (e.g., 0.5, 1.0)\n91:     MaxCPU float64\n92:     \n93:     // MaxMemory is the maximum memory in bytes\n94:     MaxMemory int64\n95:     \n96:     // MaxOutputSize is the maximum output size in bytes\n97:     MaxOutputSize int64\n98:     \n99:     // MaxProcesses is the maximum number of processes\n100:     MaxProcesses int\n101: }\n102: ```\n103: \n104: ### SecurityOptions\n105: \n106: ```go\n107: // SecurityOptions defines security settings for command execution\n108: type SecurityOptions struct {\n109:     // UID is the user ID to run commands as\n110:     UID int\n111:     \n112:     // GID is the group ID to run commands as\n113:     GID int\n114:     \n115:     // Capabilities is the list of allowed capabilities\n116:     Capabilities []string\n117:     \n118:     // ReadOnlyFS makes the filesystem read-only\n119:     ReadOnlyFS bool\n120:     \n121:     // NoNetwork disables network access\n122:     NoNetwork bool\n123:     \n124:     // AllowedCommands is an optional allowlist of command paths\n125:     AllowedCommands []string\n126: }\n127: ```\n128: \n129: ### Command\n130: \n131: ```go\n132: // Command represents a command to execute\n133: type Command struct {\n134:     // Path is the command path\n135:     Path string\n136:     \n137:     // Args are the command arguments\n138:     Args []string\n139:     \n140:     // Env is the environment variables\n141:     Env []string\n142:     \n143:     // Dir is the working directory\n144:     Dir string\n145:     \n146:     // Stdin is the standard input\n147:     Stdin io.Reader\n148:     \n149:     // Stdout is the standard output (optional, captured if nil)\n150:     Stdout io.Writer\n151:     \n152:     // Stderr is the standard error (optional, captured if nil)\n153:     Stderr io.Writer\n154: }\n155: ```\n156: \n157: ### CommandResult\n158: \n159: ```go\n160: // CommandResult represents the result of command execution\n161: type CommandResult struct {\n162:     // ExitCode is the process exit code\n163:     ExitCode int\n164:     \n165:     // Stdout is the captured standard output\n166:     Stdout []byte\n167:     \n168:     // Stderr is the captured standard error\n169:     Stderr []byte\n170:     \n171:     // Duration is the execution duration\n172:     Duration time.Duration\n173:     \n174:     // OOMKilled indicates if the process was killed due to OOM\n175:     OOMKilled bool\n176:     \n177:     // Timeout indicates if the command timed out\n178:     Timeout bool\n179: }\n180: ```\n181: \n182: ### Process\n183: \n184: ```go\n185: // Process represents a running process\n186: type Process struct {\n187:     // PID is the process ID\n188:     PID int\n189:     \n190:     // cmd is the underlying exec.Cmd\n191:     cmd *exec.Cmd\n192:     \n193:     // startTime is when the process started\n194:     startTime time.Time\n195: }\n196: ```\n197: \n198: ### OutputHandler\n199: \n200: ```go\n201: // OutputHandler handles streaming output\n202: type OutputHandler interface {\n203:     // OnStdout is called when stdout data is available\n204:     OnStdout(data []byte)\n205:     \n206:     // OnStderr is called when stderr data is available\n207:     OnStderr(data []byte)\n208:     \n209:     // OnComplete is called when execution completes\n210:     OnComplete(result *CommandResult)\n211: }\n212: ```\n213: \n214: ## API Contracts\n215: \n216: ### PicoD Initialization\n217: \n218: ```go\n219: // New creates a new PicoD instance\n220: func New(sandboxID string, opts ...Option) *PicoD\n221: \n222: // WithWorkDir sets the working directory\n223: func WithWorkDir(dir string) Option\n224: \n225: // WithLimits sets resource limits\n226: func WithLimits(limits *ResourceLimits) Option\n227: \n228: // WithSecurityOpts sets security options\n229: func WithSecurityOpts(opts *SecurityOptions) Option\n230: \n231: // WithLogger sets the logger\n232: func WithLogger(logger klog.Logger) Option\n233: ```\n234: \n235: ### Command Execution\n236: \n237: ```go\n238: // Run executes a command and waits for completion\n239: func (p *PicoD) Run(ctx context.Context, cmd *Command) (*CommandResult, error)\n240: \n241: // Start starts a command without waiting\n242: func (p *PicoD) Start(ctx context.Context, cmd *Command) (*Process, error)\n243: \n244: // RunWithStreaming executes a command with streaming output\n245: func (p *PicoD) RunWithStreaming(ctx context.Context, cmd *Command, handler OutputHandler) (*CommandResult, error)\n246: ```\n247: \n248: ### Process Management\n249: \n250: ```go\n251: // Wait waits for the process to complete\n252: func (p *Process) Wait() (*CommandResult, error)\n253: \n254: // Kill sends a signal to the process\n255: func (p *Process) Kill(signal os.Signal) error\n256: \n257: // Signal sends a specific signal to the process\n258: func (p *Process) Signal(sig syscall.Signal) error\n259: ```\n260: \n261: ### Resource Limits\n262: \n263: ```go\n264: // DefaultResourceLimits returns default resource limits\n265: func DefaultResourceLimits() *ResourceLimits\n266: \n267: // Validate validates resource limits\n268: func (l *ResourceLimits) Validate() error\n269: \n270: // Apply applies resource limits to a process\n271: func (l *ResourceLimits) Apply(cmd *exec.Cmd) error\n272: ```\n273: \n274: ### Security Validation\n275: \n276: ```go\n277: // DefaultSecurityOpts returns default security options\n278: func DefaultSecurityOpts() *SecurityOptions\n279: \n280: // Validate validates security options\n281: func (o *SecurityOptions) Validate() error\n282: \n283: // ValidateCommand validates a command for security\n284: func ValidateCommand(cmd *Command, opts *SecurityOptions) error\n285: \n286: // IsPathSafe checks if a path is within the allowed workspace\n287: func IsPathSafe(path, workDir string) bool\n288: ```\n289: \n290: ### Configuration\n291: \n292: ```go\n293: // LoadConfig loads configuration from environment variables\n294: func LoadConfig() (*Config, error)\n295: \n296: // Config holds PicoD configuration\n297: type Config struct {\n298:     WorkDir         string\n299:     DefaultTimeout  time.Duration\n300:     MaxMemory       int64\n301:     MaxCPU          float64\n302:     MaxOutputSize   int64\n303:     MaxProcesses    int\n304: }\n305: ```\n306: \n307: ## Error Handling\n308: \n309: ### ExecutionError\n310: \n311: ```go\n312: // ExecutionError represents an execution error\n313: type ExecutionError struct {\n314:     // Type is the error type\n315:     Type ExecutionErrorType\n316:     \n317:     // Message is the error message\n318:     Message string\n319:     \n320:     // Underlying is the underlying error\n321:     Underlying error\n322: }\n323: \n324: // Error implements the error interface\n325: func (e *ExecutionError) Error() string\n326: \n327: // Unwrap returns the underlying error\n328: func (e *ExecutionError) Unwrap() error\n329: ```\n330: \n331: ### ExecutionErrorType\n332: \n333: ```go\n334: type ExecutionErrorType string\n335: \n336: const (\n337:     ExecutionErrorTimeout    ExecutionErrorType = \"timeout\"\n338:     ExecutionErrorOOM        ExecutionErrorType = \"oom\"\n339:     ExecutionErrorCancelled  ExecutionErrorType = \"cancelled\"\n340:     ExecutionErrorSecurity   ExecutionErrorType = \"security\"\n341:     ExecutionErrorResource   ExecutionErrorType = \"resource\"\n342:     ExecutionErrorExec       ExecutionErrorType = \"exec\"\n343: )\n344: ```\n345: \n346: ### Error Conditions\n347: \n348: | Condition | Error Type | HTTP Mapping | Description |\n349: |-----------|------------|--------------|-------------|\n350: | Command exceeds timeout | `ExecutionErrorTimeout` | 408 Request Timeout | Command execution exceeded configured timeout |\n351: | Command exceeds memory | `ExecutionErrorOOM` | 413 Payload Too Large | Process was killed due to OOM |\n352: | Context cancelled | `ExecutionErrorCancelled` | 499 Client Closed Request | Client cancelled the operation |\n353: | Security violation | `ExecutionErrorSecurity` | 403 Forbidden | Command failed security validation |\n354: | Resource limit invalid | `ExecutionErrorResource` | 400 Bad Request | Invalid resource limit configuration |\n355: | Exec failure | `ExecutionErrorExec` | 500 Internal Server Error | Failed to start/execute command |\n356: \n357: ## Implementation Details\n358: \n359: ### PicoD Initialization\n360: \n361: ```go\n362: func New(sandboxID string, opts ...Option) *PicoD {\n363:     p := &PicoD{\n364:         sandboxID:    sandboxID,\n365:         workDir:      \"/tmp/picod/\" + sandboxID,\n366:         limits:       DefaultResourceLimits(),\n367:         securityOpts: DefaultSecurityOpts(),\n368:         logger:       klog.Background(),\n369:     }\n370:     \n371:     for _, opt := range opts {\n372:         opt(p)\n373:     }\n374:     \n375:     return p\n376: }\n377: ```\n378: \n379: ### Command Execution Flow\n380: \n381: ```go\n382: func (p *PicoD) Run(ctx context.Context, cmd *Command) (*CommandResult, error) {\n383:     // 1. Validate command\n384:     if err := ValidateCommand(cmd, p.securityOpts); err != nil {\n385:         return nil, &ExecutionError{\n386:             Type:    ExecutionErrorSecurity,\n387:             Message: \"command validation failed\",\n388:             Underlying: err,\n389:         }\n390:     }\n391:     \n392:     // 2. Create exec.Cmd\n393:     execCmd := exec.CommandContext(ctx, cmd.Path, cmd.Args...)\n394:     \n395:     // 3. Configure environment\n396:     execCmd.Env = cmd.Env\n397:     execCmd.Dir = cmd.Dir\n398:     \n399:     // 4. Apply resource limits\n400:     if err := p.limits.Apply(execCmd); err != nil {\n401:         return nil, &ExecutionError{\n402:             Type:    ExecutionErrorResource,\n403:             Message: \"failed to apply resource limits\",\n404:             Underlying: err,\n405:         }\n406:     }\n407:     \n408:     // 5. Capture output\n409:     var stdoutBuf, stderrBuf bytes.Buffer\n410:     if cmd.Stdout == nil {\n411:         execCmd.Stdout = &stdoutBuf\n412:     } else {\n413:         execCmd.Stdout = cmd.Stdout\n414:     }\n415:     if cmd.Stderr == nil {\n416:         execCmd.Stderr = &stderrBuf\n417:     } else {\n418:         execCmd.Stderr = cmd.Stderr\n419:     }\n420:     \n421:     // 6. Start execution\n422:     startTime := time.Now()\n423:     if err := execCmd.Start(); err != nil {\n424:         return nil, &ExecutionError{\n425:             Type:    ExecutionErrorExec,\n426:             Message: \"failed to start command\",\n427:             Underlying: err,\n428:         }\n429:     }\n430:     \n431:     // 7. Wait for completion\n432:     err := execCmd.Wait()\n433:     duration := time.Since(startTime)\n434:     \n435:     // 8. Build result\n436:     result := &CommandResult{\n437:         Duration: duration,\n438:     }\n439:     \n440:     if cmd.Stdout == nil {\n441:         result.Stdout = stdoutBuf.Bytes()\n442:     }\n443:     if cmd.Stderr == nil {\n444:         result.Stderr = stderrBuf.Bytes()\n445:     }\n446:     \n447:     // 9. Check for timeout/OOM\n448:     if ctx.Err() == context.DeadlineExceeded {\n449:         result.Timeout = true\n450:         err = &ExecutionError{\n451:             Type:    ExecutionErrorTimeout,\n452:             Message: \"command timed out\",\n453:         }\n454:     }\n455:     \n456:     if exitErr, ok := err.(*exec.ExitError); ok {\n457:         if status, ok := exitErr.Sys().(syscall.WaitStatus); ok {\n458:             if status.Signal() == syscall.SIGKILL {\n459:                 result.OOMKilled = true\n460:                 err = &ExecutionError{\n461:                     Type:    ExecutionErrorOOM,\n462:                     Message: \"process killed due to OOM\",\n463:                 }\n464:             }\n465:         }\n466:         result.ExitCode = exitErr.ExitCode()\n467:     } else if err == nil {\n468:         result.ExitCode = 0\n469:     }\n470:     \n471:     return result, err\n472: }\n473: ```\n474: \n475: ### Resource Limit Enforcement\n476: \n477: ```go\n478: func (l *ResourceLimits) Apply(cmd *exec.Cmd) error {\n479:     if cmd.SysProcAttr == nil {\n480:         cmd.SysProcAttr = &syscall.SysProcAttr{}\n481:     }\n482:     \n483:     // Set CPU limits via cgroups (Linux)\n484:     if l.MaxCPU > 0 {\n485:         // Use cpu.cfs_quota_us and cpu.cfs_period_us\n486:         // This requires cgroup setup\n487:     }\n488:     \n489:     // Set memory limits\n490:     if l.MaxMemory > 0 {\n491:         cmd.SysProcAttr.Setpgid = true\n492:         // Memory limits via setrlimit\n493:         syscall.Setrlimit(syscall.RLIMIT_AS, &syscall.Rlimit{\n494:             Cur: uint64(l.MaxMemory),\n495:             Max: uint64(l.MaxMemory),\n496:         })\n497:     }\n498:     \n499:     // Set process limits\n500:     if l.MaxProcesses > 0 {\n501:         syscall.Setrlimit(syscall.RLIMIT_NPROC, &syscall.Rlimit{\n502:             Cur: uint64(l.MaxProcesses),\n503:             Max: uint64(l.MaxProcesses),\n504:         })\n505:     }\n506:     \n507:     return nil\n508: }\n509: ```\n510: \n511: ### Security Validation\n512: \n513: ```go\n514: func ValidateCommand(cmd *Command, opts *SecurityOptions) error {\n515:     // 1. Check if command path is in allowlist\n516:     if len(opts.AllowedCommands) > 0 {\n517:         allowed := false\n518:         for _, allowedCmd := range opts.AllowedCommands {\n519:             if cmd.Path == allowedCmd {\n520:                 allowed = true\n521:                 break\n522:             }\n523:         }\n524:         if !allowed {\n525:             return fmt.Errorf(\"command %q not in allowlist\", cmd.Path)\n526:         }\n527:     }\n528:     \n529:     // 2. Validate working directory\n530:     if cmd.Dir != \"\" && !IsPathSafe(cmd.Dir, opts.WorkDir) {\n531:         return fmt.Errorf(\"working directory %q is outside workspace\", cmd.Dir)\n532:     }\n533:     \n534:     // 3. Check for path traversal in arguments\n535:     for _, arg := range cmd.Args {\n536:         if strings.Contains(arg, \"..\") {\n537:             return fmt.Errorf(\"argument %q contains path traversal\", arg)\n538:         }\n539:     }\n540:     \n541:     // 4. Validate environment variables\n542:     for _, env := range cmd.Env {\n543:         if strings.HasPrefix(env, \"LD_PRELOAD\") || strings.HasPrefix(env, \"LD_LIBRARY_PATH\") {\n544:             return fmt.Errorf(\"dangerous environment variable: %s\", env)\n545:         }\n546:     }\n547:     \n548:     return nil\n549: }\n550: \n551: func IsPathSafe(path, workDir string) bool {\n552:     absPath, err := filepath.Abs(path)\n553:     if err != nil {\n554:         return false\n555:     }\n556:     \n557:     absWorkDir, err := filepath.Abs(workDir)\n558:     if err != nil {\n559:         return false\n560:     }\n561:     \n562:     return strings.HasPrefix(absPath, absWorkDir)\n563: }\n564: ```\n565: \n566: ## Configuration\n567: \n568: ### Environment Variables\n569: \n570: | Variable | Required | Default | Notes |\n571: |----------|----------|---------|-------|\n572: | `PICOD_WORKDIR` | No | `/tmp/picod` | Base working directory |\n573: | `PICOD_DEFAULT_TIMEOUT` | No | `30s` | Default command timeout |\n574: | `PICOD_MAX_MEMORY` | No | `128Mi` | Default memory limit |\n575: | `PICOD_MAX_CPU` | No | `1.0` | Default CPU limit |\n576: | `PICOD_MAX_OUTPUT_SIZE` | No | `10MB` | Default output size limit |\n577: | `PICOD_MAX_PROCESSES` | No | `10` | Default process limit |\n578: \n579: ### Example Configuration\n580: \n581: ```go\n582: config := &Config{\n583:     WorkDir:        \"/tmp/picod\",\n584:     DefaultTimeout: 30 * time.Second,\n585:     MaxMemory:      128 * 1024 * 1024, // 128 MiB\n586:     MaxCPU:         1.0,\n587:     MaxOutputSize:  10 * 1024 * 1024, // 10 MiB\n588:     MaxProcesses:   10,\n589: }\n590: ```\n591: \n592: ## Testing Strategy\n593: \n594: ### Unit Tests\n595: \n596: | Test | Purpose |\n597: |------|---------|\n598: | `TestPicoD_Run_Success` | Basic command execution |\n599: | `TestPicoD_Run_Timeout` | Command exceeds timeout |\n600: | `TestPicoD_Run_OOM` | Command exceeds memory limit |\n601: | `TestPicoD_Run_Cancelled` | Context cancellation |\n602: | `TestPicoD_OutputCapture` | Stdout/stderr capture |\n603: | `TestPicoD_SecurityValidation` | Invalid commands rejected |\n604: | `TestPicoD_ResourceLimits_Validate` | Resource limit validation |\n605: | `TestPicoD_SecurityOpts_Validate` | Security options validation |\n606: | `TestPicoD_WithOptions` | Functional options pattern |\n607: | `TestPicoD_ExecutionErrorTypes` | Error type classification |\n608: \n609: ### Integration Tests\n610: \n611: | Test | Purpose |\n612: |------|---------|\n613: | `TestPicoD_Integration_FullLifecycle` | Full execution flow |\n614: | `TestPicoD_Integration_Concurrent` | Multiple concurrent commands |\n615: | `TestPicoD_Integration_ResourceLimits` | Verify limits are enforced |\n616: | `TestPicoD_Integration_Streaming` | Output streaming functionality |\n617: | `TestPicoD_Integration_SignalHandling` | Process signal handling |\n618: \n619: ### Test Fixtures\n620: \n621: ```go\n622: // mockOutputHandler implements OutputHandler for testing\n623: type mockOutputHandler struct {\n624:     stdoutCalls [][]byte\n625:     stderrCalls [][]byte\n626:     completeCalled bool\n627:     lastResult *CommandResult\n628: }\n629: \n630: func (m *mockOutputHandler) OnStdout(data []byte) {\n631:     m.stdoutCalls = append(m.stdoutCalls, data)\n632: }\n633: \n634: func (m *mockOutputHandler) OnStderr(data []byte) {\n635:     m.stderrCalls = append(m.stderrCalls, data)\n636: }\n637: \n638: func (m *mockOutputHandler) OnComplete(result *CommandResult) {\n639:     m.completeCalled = true\n640:     m.lastResult = result\n641: }\n642: ```\n643: \n644: ## Acceptance Criteria\n645: \n646: - [ ] `PicoD` struct implements all required methods\n647: - [ ] Resource limits are enforced (timeout, CPU, memory, output size)\n648: - [ ] Output capture works correctly (stdout, stderr, exit code)\n649: - [ ] Cancellation via context is supported\n650: - [ ] Security validations prevent dangerous operations\n651: - [ ] Streaming output is supported\n652: - [ ] All unit tests pass\n653: - [ ] Integration tests pass\n654: - [ ] Code coverage >= 80%\n655: - [ ] Documentation includes usage examples\n656: - [ ] Error types are properly classified and documented\n657: \n658: ## Dependencies\n659: \n660: | Package | Purpose |\n661: |---------|---------|\n662: | `context` | Command cancellation and timeouts |\n663: | `os/exec` | Command execution primitives |\n664: | `syscall` | Process management and signals |\n665: | `k8s.io/klog/v2` | Structured logging |\n666: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types` | SandboxInfo type definitions |\n667: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` | Type definitions |\n668: \n669: ## Affected Components\n670: \n671: 1. **Sandbox Manager** (`pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox/`): Will use PicoD for command execution within sandboxes\n672: 2. **Workload Manager** (`pkg/workloadmanager/`): Will invoke PicoD APIs for job execution\n673: 3. **Code Interpreter** (standalone daemon): Will use PicoD execution logic\n674: 4. **Security Module**: Will configure security policies for command execution\n675: 5. **Monitoring System**: Will collect metrics from command execution\n676: \n677: ## References\n678: \n679: - AR-012: Sandbox Infrastructure\n680: - AR-013: Session Storage\n681: - AR-014: Valkey Storage\n682: - `code-execution/spec.md`: PicoD Specification\n683: - `code-execution/design.md`: PicoD Design\n684: - `deployment/client-go.md`: Kubernetes Client-Go\n\n(End of file - total 684 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Design: AR-015 PicoD Command Execution API\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-015 — PicoD Command Execution API |\n| Module | `pkg/picod` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | M |\n| Stage | ST-1 completed |\n\nThis document describes the technical implementation for the PicoD command execution API within `pkg/picod`. The PicoD module provides secure, resource-limited command execution capabilities for the AgentCube platform, serving as the execution engine for code interpreters and agent runtimes.\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Component Structure\n\n```\npkg/picod/","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/picod/design.md","time":{"start":1775860041169,"end":1775860041223}}}}
