{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775860045778,"sessionID":"ses_2867e7541ffeWRc4IJHf3hGfjk","part":{"id":"prt_d7981d2d7001TtlMHH2QGtmIiI","messageID":"msg_d7981c65a0013dFh033nFIMWtG","sessionID":"ses_2867e7541ffeWRc4IJHf3hGfjk","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_974217226c504697b2d2adea","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-015/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-015/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-015 — PicoD 命令执行 API Tasks\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-015 — PicoD 命令执行 API |\n8: | Module | `pkg/picod` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: | Design Stage | ST-2 (In Progress) |\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Atomic Tasks\n16: \n17: ### Phase 1: Core Structure\n18: \n19: - [ ] **TASK-001**: Create `pkg/picod/picod.go`\n20:   - Define `PicoD` struct with fields:\n21:     - `sandboxID string`\n22:     - `workDir string`\n23:     - `limits *ResourceLimits`\n24:     - `securityOpts *SecurityOptions`\n25:     - `logger klog.Logger`\n26:   - Implement `New(sandboxID string, opts ...Option) *PicoD` constructor\n27: \n28: ### Phase 2: Resource Limits\n29: \n30: - [ ] **TASK-010**: Create `pkg/picod/limits.go`\n31:   - Define `ResourceLimits` struct\n32:   - Define `SecurityOptions` struct\n33:   - Implement option builder pattern:\n34:     - `WithTimeout(d time.Duration) Option`\n35:     - `WithMaxMemory(bytes int64) Option`\n36:     - `WithMaxCPU(cores float64) Option`\n37:     - `WithMaxOutputSize(bytes int64) Option`\n38:     - `WithMaxProcesses(count int) Option`\n39:     - `WithUID(uid int) Option`\n40:     - `WithGID(gid int) Option`\n41:     - `WithReadOnlyFS() Option`\n42:     - `WithNoNetwork() Option`\n43: \n44: ### Phase 3: Command Execution\n45: \n46: - [ ] **TASK-020**: Create `pkg/picod/executor.go`\n47:   - Define `Command` struct\n48:   - Define `CommandResult` struct\n49:   - Define `Process` struct\n50:   - Implement `Run(ctx context.Context, cmd *Command) (*CommandResult, error)`\n51:   - Implement `Start(ctx context.Context, cmd *Command) (*Process, error)`\n52:   - Implement `Process.Wait() (*CommandResult, error)`\n53:   - Implement `Process.Kill(signal os.Signal) error`\n54: \n55: ### Phase 4: Output Handling\n56: \n57: - [ ] **TASK-030**: Create `pkg/picod/output.go`\n58:   - Implement output capture with size limits\n59:   - Implement streaming output support\n60:   - Implement output buffer management\n61: \n62: ### Phase 5: Security\n63: \n64: - [ ] **TASK-040**: Create `pkg/picod/security.go`\n65:   - Implement command validation\n66:   - Implement allowlist checking\n67:   - Implement path traversal prevention\n68:   - Implement capability dropping\n69: \n70: ### Phase 6: Testing (TDD)\n71: \n72: #### Unit Tests\n73: \n74: - [ ] **TEST-001**: Create `pkg/picod/picod_test.go`\n75:   - Test `New()` with various options\n76:   - Test option builder functions\n77: \n78: - [ ] **TEST-010**: Test `Run()` success case\n79: - [ ] **TEST-011**: Test `Run()` timeout\n80: - [ ] **TEST-012**: Test `Run()` cancellation\n81: - [ ] **TEST-013**: Test `Run()` output capture\n82: - [ ] **TEST-014**: Test `Run()` exit code handling\n83: \n84: - [ ] **TEST-020**: Test `Start()` and `Wait()` lifecycle\n85: - [ ] **TEST-021**: Test `Process.Kill()`\n86: \n87: - [ ] **TEST-030**: Test output size limits\n88: - [ ] **TEST-031**: Test streaming output\n89: \n90: - [ ] **TEST-040**: Test security validations\n91: - [ ] **TEST-041**: Test allowlist enforcement\n92: - [ ] **TEST-042**: Test path traversal prevention\n93: \n94: #### Integration Tests\n95: \n96: - [ ] **TEST-050**: Create `pkg/picod/picod_integration_test.go`\n97: - [ ] **TEST-051**: Integration test full lifecycle\n98: - [ ] **TEST-052**: Integration test concurrent execution\n99: - [ ] **TEST-053**: Integration test resource limits enforcement\n100: \n101: ### Phase 7: Documentation\n102: \n103: - [ ] **DOC-001**: Add godoc comments to all exported types\n104: - [ ] **DOC-002**: Add godoc comments to all exported functions\n105: - [ ] **DOC-003**: Add usage examples\n106: - [ ] **DOC-004**: Document security considerations\n107: \n108: ---\n109: \n110: ## Acceptance Criteria\n111: \n112: - [ ] `PicoD` struct implements all required methods\n113: - [ ] Resource limits are enforced (timeout, CPU, memory, output size)\n114: - [ ] Output capture and streaming work correctly\n115: - [ ] Cancellation via context is supported\n116: - [ ] Security validations prevent dangerous operations\n117: - [ ] All unit tests pass\n118: - [ ] Integration tests pass\n119: - [ ] Code coverage >= 80%\n120: - [ ] Godoc documentation complete\n121: \n122: ---\n123: \n124: ## Dependencies\n125: \n126: | Dependency | Source | Usage |\n127: |------------|--------|-------|\n128: | `context` | Standard | Command cancellation |\n129: | `os/exec` | Standard | Command execution |\n130: | `syscall` | Standard | Process management |\n131: | `k8s.io/klog/v2` | External | Logging |\n132: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types` | Internal | Type definitions |\n133: \n134: ---\n135: \n136: ## Implementation Order\n137: \n138: ```\n139: TASK-001\n140:     ↓\n141: TASK-010\n142:     ↓\n143: TASK-020\n144:     ↓\n145: TASK-030\n146:     ↓\n147: TASK-040\n148:     ↓\n149: TEST-001 → TEST-053\n150:     ↓\n151: DOC-001 → DOC-004\n152: ```\n153: \n154: ---\n155: \n156: ## Related ARs\n157: \n158: | AR | Title | Relationship |\n159: |----|-------|--------------|\n160: | AR-012 | Session Storage Interface | Base infrastructure |\n161: | AR-013 | Redis Storage Implementation | Storage backend |\n162: | AR-014 | Valkey Storage Implementation | Storage backend |\n163: | AR-015 | PicoD 命令执行 API | This implementation |\n\n(End of file - total 163 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-015 — PicoD 命令执行 API Tasks\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-015 — PicoD 命令执行 API |\n| Module | `pkg/picod` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | M |\n| Design Stage | ST-2 (In Progress) |\n\n---\n\n## Atomic Tasks\n\n### Phase 1: Core Structure\n\n- [ ] **TASK-001**: Create `pkg/picod/picod.go`\n  - Define `PicoD` struct with fields:","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-015/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775860045765,"end":1775860045775}}}}
