{"type":"text","timestamp":1775860048960,"sessionID":"ses_2867e7541ffeWRc4IJHf3hGfjk","part":{"id":"prt_d7981e1b700127ZgJCQap7rnO9","messageID":"msg_d7981d7ff001T36my6rI5Asnk0","sessionID":"ses_2867e7541ffeWRc4IJHf3hGfjk","type":"text","text":"Based on the AR-016 proposal and existing codebase structure, I'll create a comprehensive tasks.md checklist with atomic, independently verifiable tasks.","time":{"start":1775860048956,"end":1775860048956}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775860143288,"sessionID":"ses_2867e7541ffeWRc4IJHf3hGfjk","part":{"id":"prt_d7981e43f001cP3YoXqCWgny5H","messageID":"msg_d7981d7ff001T36my6rI5Asnk0","sessionID":"ses_2867e7541ffeWRc4IJHf3hGfjk","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_97d3942226cd4bb78ae1172c","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-016 — PicoD 文件管理 API Tasks\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-016 — PicoD 文件管理 API |\n| Module | `pkg/picod` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | M |\n| Stage | ST-3 completed |\n\n## Atomic Tasks\n\n### Phase 1: Core Data Structures & Types\n\n- [ ] **TASK-001**: Define `FileType` type and constants in `pkg/picod/fileinfo.go`\n  - Types: `FileTypeRegular`, `FileTypeDirectory`, `FileTypeSymlink`, `FileTypeOther`\n  - String representation for each type\n\n- [ ] **TASK-002**: Define `FileInfo` struct in `pkg/picod/fileinfo.go`\n  - Fields: `Name` (string), `Path` (string), `Size` (int64), `Mode` (os.FileMode), `ModTime` (time.Time), `IsDir` (bool), `FileType` (FileType)\n  - Constructor: `NewFileInfo(path string, info os.FileInfo) (*FileInfo, error)`\n\n- [ ] **TASK-003**: Define `FileQuota` struct in `pkg/picod/quota.go`\n  - Fields: `MaxFileSize` (int64), `MaxTotalSize` (int64), `MaxFiles` (int64), `MaxDirectoryDepth` (int)\n  - Method: `Validate()` returning error\n  - Validation rules: MaxFileSize > 0, MaxTotalSize > 0, MaxFiles > 0, MaxDirectoryDepth > 0\n\n- [ ] **TASK-004**: Define `DefaultFileQuota()` function in `pkg/picod/quota.go`\n  - Returns: MaxFileSize=10MB, MaxTotalSize=100MB, MaxFiles=1000, MaxDirectoryDepth=10\n\n- [ ] **TASK-005**: Define `QuotaUsage` struct in `pkg/picod/quota.go`\n  - Fields: `UsedBytes` (int64), `MaxBytes` (int64), `FileCount` (int64), `MaxFiles` (int64), `PercentUsed` (float64)\n\n- [ ] **TASK-006**: Define `FileErrorType` and error constants in `pkg/picod/errors.go`\n  - Types: `FileErrorNotFound`, `FileErrorPermission`, `FileErrorQuotaExceeded`, `FileErrorPathTraversal`, `FileErrorWrite`, `FileErrorRead`, `FileErrorSymlink`, `FileErrorDepth`\n\n- [ ] **TASK-007**: Define `FileError` struct in `pkg/picod/errors.go`\n  - Fields: `Type` (FileErrorType), `Message` (string), `Underlying` (error)\n  - Methods: `Error()`, `Unwrap()`\n\n### Phase 2: Path Validation Utilities\n\n- [ ] **TASK-010**: Implement `ValidatePath()` function in `pkg/picod/path.go`\n  - Validates path is within workspace boundary\n  - Returns absolute path or error\n  - Prevents path traversal attacks\n\n- [ ] **TASK-011**: Implement `ResolvePath()` function in `pkg/picod/path.go`\n  - Resolves path to absolute, following symlinks\n  - Returns error if symlink target is outside workspace\n\n- [ ] **TASK-012**: Implement `GetDepth()` function in `pkg/picod/path.go`\n  - Calculates directory depth of a path\n  - Returns depth as integer\n\n- [ ] **TASK-013**: Implement `IsWithinWorkspace()` function in `pkg/picod/path.go`\n  - Checks if resolved path is within workspace\n  - Uses filepath.Abs and strings.HasPrefix\n\n- [ ] **TASK-014**: Implement `ValidateDepth()` function in `pkg/picod/path.go`\n  - Validates path depth does not exceed maximum\n  - Returns error if depth exceeds limit\n\n### Phase 3: FileSystem Interface Definition\n\n- [ ] **TASK-020**: Define `FileSystem` interface in `pkg/picod/filesystem.go`\n  - Methods:\n    - `Read(ctx context.Context, path string) ([]byte, error)`\n    - `ReadStream(ctx context.Context, path string) (io.ReadCloser, error)`\n    - `Write(ctx context.Context, path string, data []byte) error`\n    - `WriteStream(ctx context.Context, path string, reader io.Reader, size int64) error`\n    - `Delete(ctx context.Context, path string) error`\n    - `DeleteAll(ctx context.Context, path string) error`\n    - `Exists(ctx context.Context, path string) (bool, error)`\n    - `Info(ctx context.Context, path string) (*FileInfo, error)`\n    - `List(ctx context.Context, path string) ([]FileInfo, error)`\n    - `Mkdir(ctx context.Context, path string, perm os.FileMode) error`\n    - `MkdirAll(ctx context.Context, path string, perm os.FileMode) error`\n    - `Rename(ctx context.Context, oldPath, newPath string) error`\n    - `Copy(ctx context.Context, srcPath, dstPath string) error`\n    - `Quota(ctx context.Context) (*QuotaUsage, error)`\n\n- [ ] **TASK-021**: Define `fileSystem` struct in `pkg/picod/filesystem.go`\n  - Fields: `workDir` (string), `quota` (*FileQuota), `logger` (klog.Logger)\n  - Implements FileSystem interface\n\n- [ ] **TASK-022**: Implement `NewFileSystem()` constructor in `pkg/picod/filesystem.go`\n  - Creates fileSystem instance with workDir, quota, logger\n\n### Phase 4: File Read Operations\n\n- [ ] **TASK-030**: Implement `Read()` method in `pkg/picod/filesystem.go`\n  - Flow: ValidatePath → Check exists → Read file → Return []byte\n  - Handle FileErrorNotFound, FileErrorPathTraversal, FileErrorRead\n\n- [ ] **TASK-031**: Implement `ReadStream()` method in `pkg/picod/filesystem.go`\n  - Opens file with streaming support\n  - Returns io.ReadCloser\n  - Validates path before opening\n\n### Phase 5: File Write Operations\n\n- [ ] **TASK-040**: Implement `Write()` method in `pkg/picod/filesystem.go`\n  - Flow: ValidatePath → Check quota → Write temp file → Atomic rename\n  - Uses temporary file + os.Rename for atomicity\n  - Handle FileErrorQuotaExceeded, FileErrorWrite\n\n- [ ] **TASK-041**: Implement `WriteStream()` method in `pkg/picod/filesystem.go`\n  - Writes from io.Reader with size limit\n  - Enforces MaxFileSize quota during write\n  - Atomic write using temp file\n\n- [ ] **TASK-042**: Implement `calculateQuotaUsage()` helper in `pkg/picod/quota.go`\n  - Walks directory tree to calculate total size and file count\n  - Returns current quota usage statistics\n\n### Phase 6: File Delete Operations\n\n- [ ] **TASK-050**: Implement `Delete()` method in `pkg/picod/filesystem.go`\n  - Removes single file or empty directory\n  - Validates path before deletion\n  - Handle FileErrorNotFound, FileErrorPermission\n\n- [ ] **TASK-051**: Implement `DeleteAll()` method in `pkg/picod/filesystem.go`\n  - Removes directory and all contents recursively\n  - Uses os.RemoveAll with path validation\n  - Logs deletion for audit trail\n\n### Phase 7: File Metadata Operations\n\n- [ ] **TASK-060**: Implement `Exists()` method in `pkg/picod/filesystem.go`\n  - Checks if path exists\n  - Returns (bool, error)\n  - Handles path validation\n\n- [ ] **TASK-061**: Implement `Info()` method in `pkg/picod/filesystem.go`\n  - Returns file metadata as *FileInfo\n  - Uses os.Stat and NewFileInfo\n  - Handle FileErrorNotFound\n\n- [ ] **TASK-062**: Implement `List()` method in `pkg/picod/filesystem.go`\n  - Lists directory contents\n  - Returns []FileInfo\n  - Reads directory with os.ReadDir\n  - Filters and validates each entry\n\n### Phase 8: Directory Operations\n\n- [ ] **TASK-070**: Implement `Mkdir()` method in `pkg/picod/filesystem.go`\n  - Creates single directory\n  - Validates depth limit\n  - Handle FileErrorDepth, FileErrorWrite\n\n- [ ] **TASK-071**: Implement `MkdirAll()` method in `pkg/picod/filesystem.go`\n  - Creates directory and all parent directories\n  - Validates depth limit for full path\n  - Handle FileErrorDepth\n\n### Phase 9: File Move/Copy Operations\n\n- [ ] **TASK-080**: Implement `Rename()` method in `pkg/picod/filesystem.go`\n  - Renames/moves file or directory\n  - Validates both oldPath and newPath\n  - Ensures target is within workspace\n  - Handle FileErrorPathTraversal\n\n- [ ] **TASK-081**: Implement `Copy()` method in `pkg/picod/filesystem.go`\n  - Copies file from srcPath to dstPath\n  - Validates both paths\n  - Checks quota before copy\n  - Preserves file permissions\n\n### Phase 10: Quota Management\n\n- [ ] **TASK-090**: Implement `Quota()` method in `pkg/picod/filesystem.go`\n  - Returns current quota usage\n  - Calls calculateQuotaUsage\n  - Calculates PercentUsed\n\n- [ ] **TASK-091**: Implement `checkWriteQuota